w is the theme that unified the body of his work. In the history of that struggle, Understanding and Being plays a central role. Published a year after his profound and complex Insight, it is the edited transcription of some thirty hours of Lonergan's lectures on that seminal book. Understanding and Being serves as a guide to the very challenging terrain of Insight, or, as one commentator put it, if Insight is the Everest in the range of Lonergan's works, Understanding and Being is the approach through rolling foothills. This edition, the second, incorporates more of the historical setting in the text and adds a wealth of explanatory notes, as well as previously unedited discussions that followed the lectures.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aComprehension (Theory of knowledge). 0aElectronic books. -- local. 0aEthics. 0aKnowledge, Theory of. 0aLonergan, Bernard J. F. -- Insight. 0aOntology. 0aSelf-knowledge, Theory of. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Religious.2bisacsh1 aCrowe, Frederick E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMorelli, Elizabeth, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMorelli, Mark, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999z978311049094740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144268288740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442682887423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442682887.jpg  a978-3-11-049094-7  University of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999c1933d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK